    management: ["Always ensure adequate sedation and analgesia BEFORE and DURING paralysis (patient is aware but unable to communicate)", "Secure definitive airway before administering NMBAs (no spontaneous ventilation)", "Rapid sequence intubation: succinylcholine 1-1.5 mg/kg IV or rocuronium 1.2 mg/kg IV", "Maintain mechanical ventilation throughout paralysis", "Sugammadex for immediate reversal of rocuronium/vecuronium at any depth of block", "Neostigmine + glycopyrrolate for reversal of non-depolarizing agents (only at TOF ≥2/4)", "Dantrolene for malignant hyperthermia triggered by succinylcholine", "Eye care (lubricant, taping) to prevent corneal desiccation during paralysis"],
    nursingActions: ["Verify BIS monitoring or adequate sedation protocol before paralytic administration", "Perform TOF monitoring every 4 hours and before redosing to avoid over-paralysis", "Provide eye care every 2 hours (artificial tears, eye taping) — blink reflex is abolished", "Reposition patient every 2 hours for pressure injury prevention (patient cannot move)", "Maintain mechanical ventilation alarms and backup equipment at bedside", "Monitor for signs of awareness: tachycardia, hypertension, lacrimation (patient cannot verbalize)", "Suction airway as needed (cough reflex abolished)", "Document TOF results, sedation scores, and all paralytic doses"],
